#. <section class="sutta" id="mn116"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn116:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 116"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 116"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn116:0.2"
msgid "Isigilisutta"
msgstr "At Isigili"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.68"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn116:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn116:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati isigilismiṃ pabbate."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Isigili Mountain."

msgctxt "mn116:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "mn116:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "mn116:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn116:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn116:2.1"
msgid "“Passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, etaṃ vebhāraṃ pabbatan”ti?"
msgstr "“Mendicants, do you see that Mount Vebhāra?”"

msgctxt "mn116:2.2"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "mn116:2.3"
msgid ""
"“Etassapi kho, bhikkhave, vebhārassa pabbatassa aññāva samaññā ahosi aññā "
"paññatti."
msgstr "“It used to have a different label and description."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn116:2.4"
msgid "Passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, etaṃ paṇḍavaṃ pabbatan”ti?"
msgstr "Do you see that Mount Paṇḍava?”"

msgctxt "mn116:2.5"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "mn116:2.6"
msgid ""
"“Etassapi kho, bhikkhave, paṇḍavassa pabbatassa aññāva samaññā ahosi aññā "
"paññatti."
msgstr "“It too used to have a different label and description."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn116:2.7"
msgid "Passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, etaṃ vepullaṃ pabbatan”ti?"
msgstr "Do you see that Mount Vepulla?”"

msgctxt "mn116:2.8"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "mn116:2.9"
msgid ""
"“Etassapi kho, bhikkhave, vepullassa pabbatassa aññāva samaññā ahosi aññā "
"paññatti."
msgstr "“It too used to have a different label and description."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn116:2.10"
msgid "Passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, etaṃ gijjhakūṭaṃ pabbatan”ti?"
msgstr "Do you see that Mount Vulture’s Peak?”"

msgctxt "mn116:2.11"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "mn116:2.12"
msgid ""
"“Etassapi kho, bhikkhave, gijjhakūṭassa pabbatassa aññāva samaññā ahosi aññā "
"paññatti."
msgstr "“It too used to have a different label and description."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn116:2.13"
msgid "Passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, imaṃ isigiliṃ pabbatan”ti?"
msgstr "Do you see that Mount Isigili?”"

msgctxt "mn116:2.14"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
msgctxt "mn116:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Imassa kho pana, bhikkhave, isigilissa pabbatassa esāva samaññā ahosi esā "
"paññatti."
msgstr "“It used to have exactly the same label and description."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.69"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn116:3.2"
msgid ""
"Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, pañca paccekabuddhasatāni imasmiṃ isigilismiṃ "
"pabbate ciranivāsino ahesuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Once upon a time, five hundred Buddhas awakened for themselves dwelt for a "
"long time on this Isigili."

msgctxt "mn116:3.3"
msgid "Te imaṃ pabbataṃ pavisantā dissanti, paviṭṭhā na dissanti."
msgstr ""
"They were seen entering the mountain, but after entering were seen no more."

msgctxt "mn116:3.4"
msgid "Tamenaṃ manussā disvā evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "When people noticed this they said:"

#. VAR: isī → isayo (mr)
msgctxt "mn116:3.5"
msgid "‘ayaṃ pabbato ime isī gilatī’ti;"
msgstr "‘That mountain swallows these hermits!’"

msgctxt "mn116:3.6"
msgid "‘isigili isigili’ tveva samaññā udapādi."
msgstr "That’s how it came to be known as Isigili."

#. VAR: Ācikkhissāmi → acikkhissāmi vo (mr)
msgctxt "mn116:3.7"
msgid "Ācikkhissāmi, bhikkhave, paccekabuddhānaṃ nāmāni;"
msgstr "I shall declare the names of the Buddhas awakened for themselves;"

msgctxt "mn116:3.8"
msgid "kittayissāmi, bhikkhave, paccekabuddhānaṃ nāmāni;"
msgstr "I shall extol the names of the Buddhas awakened for themselves;"

msgctxt "mn116:3.9"
msgid "desessāmi, bhikkhave, paccekabuddhānaṃ nāmāni."
msgstr "I shall teach the names of the Buddhas awakened for themselves."

msgctxt "mn116:3.10"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "mn116:3.11"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn116:3.12"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn116:4.1"
msgid ""
"“Ariṭṭho nāma, bhikkhave, paccekasambuddho imasmiṃ isigilismiṃ pabbate "
"ciranivāsī ahosi;"
msgstr ""
"“The Buddhas awakened for themselves who dwelt for a long time on this "
"Isigili were named Ariṭṭha,"

msgctxt "mn116:4.2"
msgid ""
"upariṭṭho nāma, bhikkhave, paccekasambuddho imasmiṃ isigilismiṃ pabbate "
"ciranivāsī ahosi;"
msgstr "Upariṭṭha,"

#. VAR: tagarasikhī → taggarasikhī (s1, mr)
msgctxt "mn116:4.3"
msgid ""
"tagarasikhī nāma, bhikkhave, paccekasambuddho imasmiṃ isigilismiṃ pabbate "
"ciranivāsī ahosi;"
msgstr "Tagarasikhin,"

msgctxt "mn116:4.4"
msgid ""
"yasassī nāma, bhikkhave, paccekasambuddho imasmiṃ isigilismiṃ pabbate "
"ciranivāsī ahosi;"
msgstr "Yasassin,"

msgctxt "mn116:4.5"
msgid ""
"sudassano nāma, bhikkhave, paccekasambuddho imasmiṃ isigilismiṃ pabbate "
"ciranivāsī ahosi;"
msgstr "Sudassana,"

msgctxt "mn116:4.6"
msgid ""
"piyadassī nāma, bhikkhave, paccekasambuddho imasmiṃ isigilismiṃ pabbate "
"ciranivāsī ahosi;"
msgstr "Piyadassin,"

msgctxt "mn116:4.7"
msgid ""
"gandhāro nāma, bhikkhave, paccekasambuddho imasmiṃ isigilismiṃ pabbate "
"ciranivāsī ahosi;"
msgstr "Gandhāra,"

msgctxt "mn116:4.8"
msgid ""
"piṇḍolo nāma, bhikkhave, paccekasambuddho imasmiṃ isigilismiṃ pabbate "
"ciranivāsī ahosi;"
msgstr "Piṇḍola,"

msgctxt "mn116:4.9"
msgid ""
"upāsabho nāma, bhikkhave, paccekasambuddho imasmiṃ isigilismiṃ pabbate "
"ciranivāsī ahosi;"
msgstr "Upāsabha,"

msgctxt "mn116:4.10"
msgid ""
"nīto nāma, bhikkhave, paccekasambuddho imasmiṃ isigilismiṃ pabbate "
"ciranivāsī ahosi;"
msgstr "Nītha,"

msgctxt "mn116:4.11"
msgid ""
"tatho nāma, bhikkhave, paccekasambuddho imasmiṃ isigilismiṃ pabbate "
"ciranivāsī ahosi, "
msgstr "Tatha, "

msgctxt "mn116:4.12"
msgid ""
"sutavā nāma, bhikkhave, paccekasambuddho imasmiṃ isigilismiṃ pabbate "
"ciranivāsī ahosi;"
msgstr "Sutavā,"

msgctxt "mn116:4.13"
msgid ""
"bhāvitatto nāma, bhikkhave, paccekasambuddho imasmiṃ isigilismiṃ pabbate "
"ciranivāsī ahosi."
msgstr "and Bhāvitatta"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn116:5.1"
msgid "Ye sattasārā anīghā nirāsā,"
msgstr "Those saintly beings, untroubled and free of hope,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:5.2"
msgid "Paccekamevajjhagamaṃsu bodhiṃ;"
msgstr "who each achieved awakening by themselves;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:5.3"
msgid "Tesaṃ visallāna naruttamānaṃ,"
msgstr "hear me extol their names,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:5.4"
msgid "Nāmāni me kittayato suṇātha."
msgstr "the supreme persons, free of thorns."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn116:5.5"
msgid "Ariṭṭho upariṭṭho tagarasikhī yasassī,"
msgstr "Ariṭṭha, Upariṭṭha, Tagarasikhin, Yasassin,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: susambuddho → buddho (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn116:5.6"
msgid "Sudassano piyadassī ca susambuddho;"
msgstr "Sudassana, and Piyadassin the awakened;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:5.7"
msgid "Gandhāro piṇḍolo upāsabho ca,"
msgstr "Gandhāra, Piṇḍola, and Upāsabha,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:5.8"
msgid "Nīto tatho sutavā bhāvitatto."
msgstr "Nītha, Tatha, Sutavā, and Bhāvitatta."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.70"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
#. VAR: matulo → methulo (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn116:6.1"
msgid "Sumbho subho matulo aṭṭhamo ca,"
msgstr "Sumbha, Subha, Methula, and Aṭṭhama,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Athassumegho → aṭṭhasumedho (mr)
msgctxt "mn116:6.2"
msgid "Athassumegho anīgho sudāṭho;"
msgstr "and Assumegha, Anīgha, and Sudāṭha,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:6.3"
msgid "Paccekabuddhā bhavanettikhīṇā,"
msgstr "awakened for themselves, enders of the attachment to rebirth."

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:6.4"
msgid "Hiṅgū ca hiṅgo ca mahānubhāvā."
msgstr "Hiṅgū, and Hiṅga the mighty."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "mn116:6.5"
msgid "Dve jālino munino aṭṭhako ca,"
msgstr "Two sages named Jāli, and Aṭṭhaka."

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:6.6"
msgid "Atha kosallo buddho atho subāhu;"
msgstr "Then the Buddha Kosala and Subāhu;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:6.7"
msgid "Upanemiso nemiso santacitto,"
msgstr "Upanemi, Nemi, and Santacitta,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:6.8"
msgid "Sacco tatho virajo paṇḍito ca."
msgstr "right and true, stainless and astute."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn116:6.9"
msgid "Kāḷūpakāḷā vijito jito ca,"
msgstr "Kāḷa and Upakāḷa, Vijita and Jita,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: guttijito → guticchito (s1-3)
msgctxt "mn116:6.10"
msgid "Aṅgo ca paṅgo ca guttijito ca;"
msgstr "Aṅga and Paṅga, and Guttijita too;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:6.11"
msgid "Passi jahi upadhidukkhamūlaṃ,"
msgstr "Passin gave up attachment, suffering’s root,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:6.12"
msgid "Aparājito mārabalaṃ ajesi."
msgstr "while Aparājita defeated Māra’s power."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "mn116:6.13"
msgid "Satthā pavattā sarabhaṅgo lomahaṃso,"
msgstr "Satthar, Pavattar, Sarabhaṅga, Lomahaṁsa,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:6.14"
msgid "Uccaṅgamāyo asito anāsavo;"
msgstr "Uccaṅgamāya, Asita, Anāsava,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:6.15"
msgid "Manomayo mānacchido ca bandhumā,"
msgstr "Manomaya, and Bandhumant the cutter of conceit,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:6.16"
msgid "Tadādhimutto vimalo ca ketumā."
msgstr "and Tadādhimutta the immaculate and resplendent."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn116:6.17"
msgid "Ketumbharāgo ca mātaṅgo ariyo,"
msgstr "Ketumbarāga, Mātaṅga, and Ariya,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:6.18"
msgid "Athaccuto accutagāmabyāmako;"
msgstr "then Accuta, Accutagāma, and Byāmaka,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:6.19"
msgid "Sumaṅgalo dabbilo supatiṭṭhito,"
msgstr "Sumaṅgala, Dabbila, Supatiṭṭhita,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:6.20"
msgid "Asayho khemābhirato ca sorato."
msgstr "Asayha, Khemābhirata, and Sorata."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "mn116:6.21"
msgid "Durannayo saṅgho athopi ujjayo,"
msgstr "Durannaya, Saṅgha, and also Ujjaya,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:6.22"
msgid "Aparo muni sayho anomanikkamo;"
msgstr "another sage, Sayha of peerless effort."

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:6.23"
msgid "Ānando nando upanando dvādasa,"
msgstr "There are twelve Ānandas, Nandas, and Upanandas,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:6.24"
msgid "Bhāradvājo antimadehadhārī."
msgstr "and Bhāradvāja, bearing his final body."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "mn116:6.25"
msgid "Bodhi mahānāmo athopi uttaro,"
msgstr "Bodhi, also Mahānāma the supreme,"

# Not sure why BB takes these as descriptions of Bharadvaja, it sounds unlikely that a paccekabuddha would be described as “beautiful, with crested mane”! Comm is silent here, which I take as endorsing the default, i.e. a straight list of names.
#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:6.26"
msgid "Kesī sikhī sundaro dvārabhājo;"
msgstr "Kesin, Sikhin, Sundara, and Bhāradvāja,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:6.27"
msgid "Tissūpatissā bhavabandhanacchidā,"
msgstr "Tissa and Upatissa, who’ve both cut the bonds to rebirth,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Upasikhi taṇhacchido ca sikhari → upasīdarī taṇhacchido ca sīdarī (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn116:6.28"
msgid "Upasikhi taṇhacchido ca sikhari."
msgstr "Upasīdarin and Sīdarin, who’ve both cut off craving."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "mn116:6.29"
msgid "Buddho ahu maṅgalo vītarāgo,"
msgstr "Maṅgala was awakened, free of greed,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:6.30"
msgid "Usabhacchidā jāliniṃ dukkhamūlaṃ;"
msgstr "Usabha cut the net, the root of suffering,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:6.31"
msgid "Santaṃ padaṃ ajjhagamopanīto,"
msgstr "Upanīta who attained the state of peace,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:6.32"
msgid "Uposatho sundaro saccanāmo."
msgstr "Uposatha, Sundara, and Saccanāma."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.71"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "mn116:6.33"
msgid "Jeto jayanto padumo uppalo ca,"
msgstr "Jeta, Jayanta, Paduma, and Uppala;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:6.34"
msgid "Padumuttaro rakkhito pabbato ca;"
msgstr "Padumuttara, Rakkhita, and Pabbata,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:6.35"
msgid "Mānatthaddho sobhito vītarāgo,"
msgstr "Mānatthaddha, beautiful and free of greed,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:6.36"
msgid "Kaṇho ca buddho suvimuttacitto."
msgstr "and the Buddha Kaṇha, his mind well freed."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "mn116:7.1"
msgid "Ete ca aññe ca mahānubhāvā,"
msgstr "These and other mighty ones awakened for themselves,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:7.2"
msgid "Paccekabuddhā bhavanettikhīṇā;"
msgstr "enders of the attachment to rebirth—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:7.3"
msgid "Te sabbasaṅgātigate mahesī,"
msgstr "honor these great hermits who are fully extinguished,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn116:7.4"
msgid "Parinibbute vandatha appameyye”ti."
msgstr "having got past all ties, limitless.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn116:7.5"
msgid "Isigilisuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
